General description from NED: This spiral has been classified as a "peculiar" galaxy because of its irregular arm morphology, consisting of multiple segments.
Description of CO image: A bright peak of CO emission appears southeast of the galaxy center.
SD comparison: another galaxy is to the south of NGC0337

General description from NED: This "lopsided" galaxy has one especially strong spiral arm, with the other arms appearing relatively smooth.
Description of CO image: CO emission is notably absent from the central region, but is well-detected in the arms.
HI quality comments: interference: Amp& phase show strong nonlinear changing across the bandwith and time at some short baselines, indicating strong continuum source(s) showed in sidelobes.
not many line-free channels for continuum-subtraction

General description from NED: This dwarf irregular galaxy has recently undergone a period of starburst activity, leading to the formation of two massive star clusters ("super star clusters").
Description of CO image: CO emission is confined to a few off-center blobs.

General description from NED: Weakly barred galaxy with an asymmetric outer spiral arm, in contrast to two fairly symmetric inner spiral arms.
Description of CO image: Spiral arms emanating from a horizontal bar-like structure are clearly visible in CO.

General description from NED: Early-type galaxy with tightly wound (nearly circular) spiral arms and a bright nucleus.
Description of CO image: Again, CO is only found near the nucleus.

General description from NED: Probable colliding system (based on appearance of two tidal tails) with a nuclear starburst, possibly fed by gas from the infalling companion.
Description of CO image: CARMA observations target only the inner part of the main galaxy, and reveal two closely spaced peaks near the nucleus.
SD comparison: SD flux may be underestimated because the SD beam is not large to cover the whole gal

General description from NED: This dwarf spiral galaxy in the M81 group is an example of a "pure disk" system lacking a bulge or bar.
Description of CO image: A few patches of CO emission are seen, roughly following a spiral pattern.

General description from NED: Face-on galaxy with tightly wound multiple arms and an elliptical bulge.
Description of CO image: Again CO is absent from the central regions, forming a more ringlike distribution around the bulge.
SD comparison: SD flux may be underestimated because the SD beam is not large to cover the whole gal
HI quality comments: Another galaxy is in the primary beam FOV with a velocity 2630-2740km/s

General description from NED: This dwarf spiral galaxy in the M81 group is an example of a "pure disk" system lacking a bulge or bar.
Description of CO image: A few patches of CO emission are seen, roughly following a spiral pattern.

General description from NED: Nearby, highly inclined galaxy with lots of HII regions spread throughout the disk.
Description of CO image: A central peak in CO emission, with much weaker lanes of molecular gas in the disk.

General description from NED: Face-on galaxy with tightly wound multiple arms and an elliptical bulge.
Description of CO image: Again CO is absent from the central regions, forming a more ringlike distribution around the bulge.

General description from NED: Multiple flocculent arms emanate from a bright inner ring, with a gap around the nucleus.
Description of CO image: Clumpy CO emission appears to be mainly found in the ring.

General description from NED: Probable colliding system (based on appearance of two tidal tails) with a nuclear starburst, possibly fed by gas from the infalling companion.
Description of CO image: CARMA observations target only the inner part of the main galaxy, and reveal two closely spaced peaks near the nucleus.

General description from NED: Highly inclined, early-type galaxy with a high rate of star formation for its class.
Description of CO image: Extensive CO emission is seen, including a central peak and two offset peaks on either side (possibly part of a ring).
SD comparison: SD flux may be underestimated because the SD beam is not large to cover the whole gal
HI quality comments: SDSS J111445.02+123851 is detected with HI to the south of N3593

General description from NED: This dwarf irregular galaxy has recently undergone a period of starburst activity, leading to the formation of two massive star clusters ("super star clusters").
Description of CO image: CO emission is confined to a few off-center blobs.

General description from NED: Nearby, highly inclined galaxy with lots of HII regions spread throughout the disk.
Description of CO image: A central peak in CO emission, with much weaker lanes of molecular gas in the disk.

General description from NED: Irregular, flocculent spiral structure in disk, with many filaments and knots of star formation.
Description of CO image: Remarkably asymmetric CO distribution, with most molecular gas being located in the southeast.

General description from NED: Barred galaxy with large, bright, circular bulge and relatively little star formation, mostly concentrated near nucleus and at bar ends.
Description of CO image: Again, an off-center CO clump is seen, this time to the south of the nucleus.

General description from NED: Large spiral in the Virgo cluster with prominent, asymmetric spiral arms and a small circular bulge.
Description of CO image: Magnificent spiral structure is seen in CO, with some emission between the arms as well.

General description from NED: Another Virgo galaxy with distorted spiral structure.
Description of CO image: CO emission traces the inner spiral arms.

General description from NED: Large Virgo spiral with two principal spiral arms showing multiple HII regions.
Description of CO image: CO emission is strongly concentrated near the center.

General description from NED: Dwarf spiral galaxy with similar size and luminosity to Large Magellanic Cloud.  Highly inclined, with strong dust lanes.
Description of CO image: CO is confined to a ringlike structure that is brightest at the ends as a result of our viewing angle.

General description from NED: This Virgo cluster spiral has a short, thin bar from which two prominent spiral arms emanate, and a lopsided stellar distribution.
Description of CO image: The bar shows up strongly in the CO image, along with the northern arm; CO in southern region is more patchy.

General description from NED: Weakly barred galaxy with an asymmetric outer spiral arm, in contrast to two fairly symmetric inner spiral arms.
Description of CO image: Spiral arms emanating from a horizontal bar-like structure are clearly visible in CO.

General description from NED: Nearly face-on galaxy with strong, thin spiral arms containing many HII regions.
Description of CO image: The thin arms show up strongly in CO emission.

General description from NED: Small angular size galaxy with peculiar morphology: three spiral arms all emanate from south side of bar.
Description of CO image: CO morphology is also asymmetric, with most emission coming from the bar and regions south and east from the center.
HI quality comments: an HI flow connects n5713 and n5719

General description from NED: Face-on, strongly barred galaxy with a nuclear ring of enhanced star formation.
Description of CO image: The bar is mostly devoid of molecular gas, but strong CO emission comes from two "hot spots" where gas in the bar enters the ring.
